HEADWORD: Upturn
<hw>Up*turn"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To turn up; to
direct upward; to throw up; <as>as, to <ex>upturn</ex> the ground in
plowing</as>.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧A sea of <xex>upturned</xex> faces.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>D. Webster.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>So scented the grim feature, and <qex>upturned</qex>⟦br⟧
His nostril wide into the murky air.</q> <rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

